{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionSustainable development continues to be a major objective for governments around the world, leading to numerous initiatives focused on protecting the environment and improving public health and safety.",
    "These efforts are primarily directed at reducing harmful emissions and making the most efficient use of fuels and raw materials.",
    "Although recycling offers a way to reuse certain by-products, it demands substantial effort in terms of gathering, processing, and comparing costs with those of natural raw materials.",
    "Concrete, the second most utilized material globally after water, relies heavily on cement as its main component [1].",
    "To improve the performance of concrete in both its fresh and hardened states, various materials are added to the cement mixture."
  ]
}